content: I can't tell you about personal experiences as an individual may find the test difficult or easy based on their knowledge level, and it also depends on how much effort they put in studying about australia and its culture, history, geography, and government. however, the citizenship test is designed to assess an individual's basic knowledge of australia, and with proper preparation and study of the required resource book, most applicants should be able to pass. the multiple-choice format of the test makes it easier for applicants to guess the correct answer if they're unsure. plus, if an applicant fails the test, they will have the opportunity to take it again after a certain period of time.
